<item>
            <title>[SPR-101] NoSuchMessageException hierarchical MessageSource</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-101</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think the new implementation of AbstractMessageSource causes problems in configurations with hierarchical application contexts. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is an example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The parent context does not declare any message source bean (interface ApplicationContext extends MessageSource)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The child context declares a message source with useCodeAsDefaultMessage set to true.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The childs messages source automatically gets the parent context as its parent message source set. Resolving a message code that is not declared the parent message source gets called and throws a NoSuchMessageException that is not caught by the message source of the child and thus causes runtime exceptions not expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thomas&lt;/p&gt;</description>
